column10:
What i like: Big game if you want to 100%; enemies don't one-shot you; quick loading times; Thank god you have infinite normal arrows; There is a lot of map to explore; Grappling big monsters looks cool; Feels like i'm playing a Monster Hunter game; 

What i don't like: Enemies are big bulletsponges; You can't get hit because you'll get perma staggered; Auto-save only on rest; no Quick-save/Quick-load; Pawn's AI makes them dogshit; some weapons deals no damage; no mobility to explore the map; RPG but no choices? Story too linear; Some of the magic makes you blind; no remarkable NPCs; Vocation system is lacking; Drops, Rewards and Shops are quite disappointing; The camera does not move in your favor; there's no progression through classes, certain equipment are locked behind specific Vocations, Pawns can't use cartain Vocations for some reason, 10 Levels per Vocation is too simple, there's no numbers on the skills so you don't know how much damage you deal/take, you can't choose your stats, the game says nothing about leveling so the level up feels worthless, leveling your vocation more often than not unlock useless abilities that you'll neve use; Health items are useless because you can just infinitely revive your pawns; Stamina items breakes the flow of combat because you'll need to open your inventory to use them; The camera focus on your Main Pawn all the time for no reason; Two of the same enemies have totally different health, defense and attack; 


Played on Hard Mode. This plays like a worse 'Dragon Age: Inquisition'. You CANNOT play this without mods.

One of the best RPG game that i ever played. This beautiful game has:

- many mechanics that perfectly work together;
- cool fighting system with many options;
- large and interesting world to explore;
- great story with incredibly awesome dragon Grigori boss fight and interesting plot twist with last boss;
- very good music;
- and badass huge DLC.

Really like this game and i'm highly recommended it for all gamers which loves RPG's or just want to try some new great game. Good Luck and Have Fun!

My group and curator page - https://steamcommunity.com/groups/olfashiong

Some of my highlights in this game thus far:
- Witnessing a cyclops look at my party, then decide to jump off the bridge to end his life himself;
- Having to jump of a very high ledge and smacking face first into the pavement, only to stand up and witness all 3 of my party members do the same one by one;
- Surviving by the skin of my teeth to an epic battle, only to be gangbanged by a murderswarm of bats;
- Getting to meet sweet Aelinore.

Greatest game I've ever played, no doubts about it.
